---
import StaticPageLayout from "@/infrastructure/components/layout/StaticPageLayout.astro";
import { SiteConfig } from "@/app/config/site.config";
import { Path } from "@/app/config/path.config";
---

<StaticPageLayout
  title="About Ravoid"
  description="Uncomfortable truths about SaaS infrastructure, AI agents in production, and the real cost of scaling."
>
  <h1>About Ravoid</h1>

  <p>
    Ravoid delivers sharp, no-fluff insights for engineering leaders and
    technical founders building serious SaaS and AI systems in production.
  </p>

  <p>
    We cut through the hype around AI agent frameworks, infrastructure choices,
    and cost models. Most decisions that feel obviously correct in the early
    stage quietly become expensive, or outright risky, once you hit real usage
    and scale.
  </p>

  <h2>Why Ravoid Exists</h2>

  <p>
    Too many teams waste months and six-figure budgets on “flexible” agent
    frameworks, multi-cloud setups, or token pricing models that collapse under
    pressure. Ravoid exists to show the uncomfortable trade-offs before you pay
    the price.
  </p>

  <p>
    Every article here is built on real production experience, realistic cost
    numbers, concrete scenarios across early, growth, and scale stages,
    meaningful trade-off tables, and decision frameworks that actually help you
    choose what survives scaling.
  </p>

  <h2>What You’ll Get</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>
      Opinionated breakdowns of AI agent frameworks in production, why most
      never escape pilot and what actually matters at scale.
    </li>
    <li>
      Deep infrastructure analysis: serverless vs traditional, single vendor vs
      multi-cloud, and the hidden costs engineers only discover after it’s too
      late.
    </li>
    <li>
      Realistic AI cost modeling and token economics, because “cheap at small
      volume” almost never stays cheap.
    </li>
    <li>
      Stage-specific guidance and practical mental models so you stop guessing
      and start making defensible technical decisions.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Behind Ravoid</h2>

  <div class="flex items-start gap-4 mt-6">
    <img
      src="https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4D03AQE_vcPpSpWXfA/profile-displayphoto-shrink_200_200/B4DZXKAxxqHYAY-/0/1742850957386?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=JpASrSsdp9PSQRwlnQQ8C3PYdU_q0aMiTE7NkVjbv8Y"
      alt="Framesta Fernando"
      class="w-24 h-24 rounded-full object-cover flex-shrink-0"
      width="96"
      height="96"
    />

    <div>
      <div
        class="mt-3 flex items-center flex-wrap gap-x-1.5 text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400"
      >
        <span>Written by</span>
        <span
          itemprop="author"
          class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 font-medium"
          >Framesta Fernando</span
        >
      </div>

      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
        Engineering Manager at MrScraper and former Technical Architect at DOT
        Indonesia. With over 5 years building scalable backend systems using
        NestJS, .NET, and Next.js, including leading a 24-engineer team, the
        lessons here come from decisions that were made (and sometimes painfully
        corrected) in real production environments, especially around AI agents
        and infrastructure scaling.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Join the Readers Who Want the Truth</h2>

  <p>
    If you’re responsible for systems that must stay reliable and cost-effective
    as they grow, Ravoid is built for you.
  </p>

  <p>
    Subscribe for sharp insights delivered directly, no fluff, no weekly tool
    roundups, just the hard-earned truths that matter when you’re in the
    trenches of production.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Have feedback, a war story, or a specific decision you want challenged?
    Reach out via the <a href={Path.contact}>contact page</a> or connect on <a
      href="https://linkedin.com/in/fradotech"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a
    >.
  </p>
</StaticPageLayout>
